oo-religions:
    "Could the various religions be derived forms of one and the same original mysticism?
    Do there exist common “member data” and functions, redefined over time, but tracing back to an initial body of beliefs (or notions)?
    Even just on this map, several can be found (e.g. Empedocles -> Poe).
    Just as the classes of an Object-Oriented language are redefined to fit a specific context of use, so too the original Mysticism may have been “overloaded” to fit a specific place or time.
    If that were the case, the further back you go in time — and thus in the class hierarchy — the closer you should get to the true characteristics of the Mysticism.
    Is it possible to define a hierarchy of classes descending from the abstract class <code>Creed</code>?
    Simplifying a great deal (since it's 3 a.m.): Buddha and Zoroaster influence the Greeks, who influence the Jews, who in turn influence the Christians, who eventually produce the Jehovah's Witnesses...
    Likewise (again simplifying), C++ evolved from C, and Java from C++."

